DSMDB-3127047v2 AMENDED AND RESTATED CO-TENANCY AND COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS CO-TENANCY AND COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this ???Agreement???), dated as of December ____, 2012, is made and entered into by and between ALPAUGH NORTH, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (f/k/a SPS Alpaugh North, LLC) (???Alpaugh North???), and ALPAUGH 50, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (f/k/a SPS Alpaugh 50, LLC) (???Alpaugh 50???, and together with Alpaugh North, the ???Parties,??? and each, a ???Party???). RECITALS A. Alpaugh North plans to develop, construct, own and operate a 20 MW solar power generation Project to be located on the Alpaugh North Project Site. Alpaugh North leases the Alpaugh North Project Site pursuant to the Alpaugh North Project Lease. B. Alpaugh 50 plans to develop, construct, own and operate a 50 MW solar power generation Project to be located on the Alpaugh 50 Project Site. Alpaugh 50 leases the Alpaugh 50 Project Site pursuant to the Alpaugh 50 Project Lease. C. The Alpaugh North Project and the Alpaugh 50 Project intend to utilize certain Common Facilities located on the Shared Premises in connection with their respective Projects. D. Alpaugh North and Alpaugh 50, as co-grantees, are parties to (i) the Canal Easement Agreement, (ii) the Lanting Easement Agreement, (iii) the Jimenez Easement Agreement, (iv) the Building and Parking Easement Agreement, and (v) the Road Easement Agreement, pursuant to which Alpaugh North and Alpaugh 50 hold certain easement rights with respect to the Shared Premises. E. It is anticipated that Alpaugh North will commence construction of the Alpaugh North Project prior to the commencement of construction by Alpaugh 50 of the Alpaugh North Project, and that Alpaugh North will construct the Common Facilities. F. Alpaugh North has agreed to assign, transfer, and convey to Alpaugh 50, an undivided interest, as a tenant in common, in and to the Common Facilities (???Undivided Interest???), effective as of (i) the later of the Construction Start Date of the Alpaugh 50 Project, (ii) the Effective Date of this Agreement, or (iii) the date the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (???FERC???) approves transfer of such Undivided Interest. G. Both Projects will be operated and managed by the Operator pursuant to the O&M Agreement, and the Parties intend to have the Operator be responsible for operation, maintenance and repair of the Common Facilities and to share the costs of the Operator as provided herein. H. The Parties intend to seek mutual economic benefits by jointly bearing the cost of certain Shared Expenses.

ARTICLE TWO DECLARATION OF INTENTION The Parties hereby declare that their relationship in and to the Common Facilities is and will be that of tenants in common, expressly subject, however, to the terms, conditions, limitations and requirements set forth in this Agreement. Nothing contained in this Agreement will be deemed to constitute the Parties as partners or joint venturers. ARTICLE THREE CONVEYANCE AND UNDIVIDED INTEREST IN COMMON FACILITIES AND SHARED PREMISES In exchange for payment of one dollar ($1.00) to each Party from each other Party, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged: 3.1 Transfer of Common Facilities by Alpaugh North. (a) Alpaugh North hereby Transfers to Alpaugh 50, an Undivided Interest in the amount of Alpaugh 50???s Project Percentage Interest, effective as of the later of (i) the Construction Start Date of the Alpaugh 50 Project, (ii) the Effective Date of this Agreement, or (iii) the date FERC issues an order pursuant to Section 203 of the Federal Power Act (???FPA???) approving such Transfer. (b) The Undivided Interest so Transferred will be memorialized by means of Alpaugh 50 recording the Memorandum of Transfer in the form attached hereto as Exhibit B-1, which shall be executed and acknowledged on the date of this Agreement. Alpaugh 50 will record, in the Official Records of Tulare County, California, the Memorandum of Transfer on or before two (2) business days following the later of the Construction Start Date of the Alpaugh 50 Project or the Effective Date of this Agreement. The Transfer will vest in Alpaugh 50 its Project Percentage Interest in each of the Common Facilities, such that Alpaugh North and Alpaugh 50 together, effective as of the later of the Construction Start Date of the Alpaugh 50 Project or the Effective Date of this Agreement, together shall own one hundred percent (100%) of the Common Facilities. (c) A Party???s use of any Common Facilities or the operation of its Project shall not in any way interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Party of its rights in such Common Facilities or the operation of its Project, any separate facilities or assets of such Party
7 DSMDB-3127047v2
or the use and enjoyment by such other Party of its Project Controlled Assets. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, each Party hereby consents to the development and operation of the Projects, and each of the Parties shall cooperate in good faith with the other Party???s uses of the Common Facilities for the benefit of each others' Projects as contemplated by this Agreement. No Party will use or permit the use of the Common Facilities in any manner that would create waste or nuisance, or that would jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Common Facilities or any Laws as to the Common Facilities, nor otherwise conduct or cause to be conducted operations on its Project Site or on the Shared Premises which would have similar effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Common Facilities. 3.2 Shared Premises. (a) The Shared Premises Agreements in effect on the date hereof allow for the construction, operation and maintenance of electric transmission and related facilities, roads and related facilities, and other equipment and facilities associated with the Projects along and within the Shared Premises. To the extent permitted by applicable laws and regulations and subject to the terms and conditions of the Shared Premises Agreements, each Party shall hold an undivided interest in the Shared Premises jointly, as tenants-in-common, for the joint use of the Shared Premises. Each Party shall have the right to utilize its applicable undivided interest in the Shared Premises in accordance with the terms of this Agreement and the Shared Premises Agreements. (b) Each Party???s use of the Shared Premises shall not in any way interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Party of the Shared Premises, or the use and enjoyment by the other party of the Common Facilities. 3.3 Shared Expenses; Interconnection. Each Party hereby confirms such Party???s obligation to share in the periodic payment of Shared Expenses, and agrees, severally but not jointly, to pay such Party???s Project Percentage Interest of the Shared Expenses as and when due and payable. The Parties will cause the Shared Expense Administrator, as authorized agent for each Party, to administer the collection and payment of the Shared Expenses, whether invoiced by each expense payee against a particular Project or invoiced as an aggregate expense of both Parties. Each Party will pay each invoice for Shared Expenses promptly upon, in any event within ten (10) days of, receipt of written notice thereof from the Shared Expense Administrator. As it becomes practicable and desirable, the Parties from time to time may designate additional expenses as Shared Expenses to be administered by the Shared Expense Administrator in accordance with this Section 3.3. Each further assumption of Shared Expense may be proposed by any Party, but will only be approved by an amendment to this Agreement. If any Party defaults in the payment of a Shared Expense, the other Party may make such payment, and the defaulting Party will promptly reimburse the paying Party and will owe interest on the amounts paid on such Party???s behalf at the Default Rate. 3.4 Temporary Use of Common Facilities Prior to Transfer. Effective as of the Effective Date and prior to the Transfer contemplated in Section 3.1(a), Alpaugh North grants to Alpaugh 50 the temporary right to utilize any Common Facilities to deliver energy over such Common Facilities in an amount no greater than Alpaugh 50???s Project Percentage Interest, which right shall expire when the Transfer contemplated by Section 3.1(a) is effective.

ARTICLE FOUR TERM 4.1 Term. The term of this Agreement will commence on the Effective Date, and, unless sooner terminated by mutual agreement of both Parties or the consolidation of ownership of the Common Facilities in a single Party, will continue for a term of twenty five (25) years from the Effective Date; provided that following such twenty five (25) years, the term of this Agreement shall be automatically renewed for an indefinite number of additional one (1) year terms until and unless a Party provides written notice of non-renewal to the other Party no later than three (3) months prior to the expiration of the then-existing term. 4.2 Surrender and Assignment of Undivided Interest. A Party who wishes to abandon and decommission its Project may elect to convey its Undivided Interest and assign its rights hereunder to the other Party and, thereupon, to cease to have any right, title or interest in the Common Facilities or its Undivided Interest (such Party a ???Surrendering Party???). The Surrendering Party must (a) deliver all instruments of transfer as may be necessary or appropriate to effect the conveyance of its Undivided Interest and assignment of its rights hereunder to, and which are reasonably satisfactory to, the remaining Party, (b) assign and convey to the remaining Party all its rights under this Agreement, provided, however, that (x) any such surrender of an encumbered Undivided Interest may only be surrendered with the written consent of each Secured Party that holds a security interest in such Undivided Interest and a release of such Secured Party???s security interest being provided by such Secured Party, and (y) all necessary prior FERC approvals must be obtained and all parties including the Surrendering Party must take all reasonable steps to obtain such FERC approval at the Surrendering Party???s sole cost and expense, and (c) cure all Events of Default then existing on the part of the Surrendering Party. The Surrendering Party shall remain fully responsible for, and shall pay its Project Percentage Interest of, all Shared Expenses of such Surrendering Party through the effective date of its surrender of its Undivided Interest and all costs, including reasonable attorneys??? fees, incurred by the other Party in obtaining FERC approval of such surrender. No surrender of a Party???s Undivided Interest shall relieve the Surrendering Party of any of its obligations (including but not limited to ongoing payment obligations) under this Agreement, the Shared Premises Agreements or any other agreement entered into pursuant to this Agreement, unless expressly provided for in this Agreement, or in a writing among the Parties. ARTICLE FIVE CONDITION OF PROPERTY AND COMPLIANCE WITH LAWS Alpaugh 50 accepts the Common Facilities in their condition existing as of the date of Transfer to Alpaugh 50 of a Project Percentage Interest therein, and subject to all Laws and all covenants, conditions, reservations, restrictions, easements, liens, encumbrances and other matters affecting the Common Facilities. Alpaugh North makes no warranty of any kind, express or implied with respect to the Common Facilities (except as to title to the Common Facilities by, through or under it). THE FOREGOING EXCLUSION OF ALL WARRANTIES BY ALPAUGH NORTH INCLUDES BUT IS NOT LIMITED TO IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF TITLE, SUITABILITY, MERCHANTABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. Each Party will, at such Party???s own expense, conduct and cause the Operator to conduct all permitted activities and operations with respect to any Common Facilities (i) in a safe

manner, (ii) in accordance with good operating practice, (iii) in compliance with all Laws, and (iv) without causing a material adverse effect on the other Party or the other Party???s Project. ARTICLE SIX INDEMNITY, USE AND COMPLIANCE; INSURANCE 6.1 Indemnity. Each Party, for and on behalf of itself and its agents, successors and assigns, shall defend, indemnify and hold harmless the other Party and such other Party???s directors, officers, partners, members, affiliates, employees, agents, successors and assigns, from and against any and all losses, liabilities, claims and damages suffered or incurred, to the extent they are both (i) (a) a result of the breach of this Agreement, failure to comply in any material respect with applicable Law, or the negligent acts or omissions, bad faith, gross negligence, or willful misconduct of the indemnifying Party or its directors, officers, partners, members, affiliates, employees, agents, successors and assigns, in connection with the indemnifying Party's Project, the Common Facilities or the performance of the indemnifying Party's duties and obligations under this Agreement, except to the extent caused by the indemnified Party's gross negligence or willful misconduct, or (b) are a result of outages or curtailment on the Common Facilities proximately caused by the indemnifying Party connecting its Project to the Common Facilities other than in accordance with the provisions hereof; and (ii) not otherwise covered by the insurance required by this Agreement. 6.2 Environmental Compliance. Without limiting the scope of each Party???s obligations under Section 6.1, each Party will, with respect to such Party???s Project Controlled Assets, be responsible for all investigations, studies, clean up, corrective actions or responses or remedial actions required by any governmental authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to such Party???s use, operation or ownership of such Party???s Project Controlled Assets. Each Party will have the right (but not the obligation, unless otherwise required above) to participate in the management and control of all investigations and any environmental clean up, remediation or related activities relating to such Party???s Project Controlled Assets. 6.3 No Waste or Nuisance; Maintenance; No Interference. No Party will use or permit the use of the Common Facilities in any manner that would create waste or nuisance that would have a materially adverse effect on the Common Facilities, Project Sites or both, or that would increase the rate or jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Common Facilities, Project Sites or both; nor shall any Party otherwise conduct, or cause to be conducted, operations on such Party???s Project Site which would have similar material adverse effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Common Facilities located on such Party???s Project Site. The Parties will at all times while conducting their respective operations and activities with respect to their Projects make reasonable efforts to minimize the impact of such operations and activities upon the other Party???s use of the Common Facilities. 6.4 Liens. No Party will cause or permit any lien or encumbrance to be levied against or attached to the other Party???s interests in the Common Facilities. All transfers of Undivided Interests will be free of any lien or encumbrance.

6.5 Taxes. Each Party will pay all real and personal property taxes and assessments, general or special, levied against such Party???s Project or the facilities and fixtures located thereon. All such taxes and assessments will be paid before delinquency and before any fine, interest or penalty will become due or be imposed for their non-payment. 6.6 Maintenance and Repair of Projects. Each Party shall, at its sole cost and expense, maintain in good working order and repair at all times each part of its Project which connects with or may affect the Common Facilities. 6.7 Regulatory Status. Each Party represents and warrants that it is qualified as an "exempt wholesale generator" ("EWG") as such term is defined in the Public Utility Holding Act of 2005, or a qualifying cogeneration or small power production facility, as defined in the Federal Power Act ("QF"), and the Parties each covenant to maintain their status as an EWG or a QF for so long as they are a party to this Agreement or have any interest in the Common Facilities. No Party will take any action that could adversely affect any other Party's ability to qualify as an EWG or a QF. 6.8 Outage or Disconnection. To the extent any Party's operating Project is disconnected or an outage occurs resulting in a loss of production and revenue to the Project, and the loss is a result of another Party's breach of this Agreement, the breaching Party shall reimburse the Party which suffered the loss for such loss within thirty (30) days of notice and supporting documentation of the loss, which supporting documentation shall include the applicable invoices from the applicable Party's power purchase agreement. 6.9 Insurance Requirements. Upon the later of the Construction Start Date of the Alpaugh 50 Project or the Effective Date of this Agreement, and thereafter for the duration of this Agreement the Parties shall, at their sole cost and expense, maintain the insurance policies and coverages described in Exhibit D-1. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Agreement, each Party waives any and every claim that arises or may arise in its favor against the other Party during the term of the Agreement for any and all loss of, or damage to any Common Facilities, to the extent such loss or damage is an insured event covered by the insurance to be maintained in accordance with this Agreement. 6.10 Evidence, Terms and Modification of Insurance. Upon and after the later of the Construction Start Date of the Alpaugh 50 Project or the Effective Date of this Agreement: (a) Except when the Parties are each a "named insured" under the same insurance policies required herein, each Party shall provide the other Party with insurance certificates reasonably acceptable to the other Party evidencing that insurance coverages are in compliance with this Agreement. Such insurance and certificates shall (i) name the other Party as an additional insureds under the policies to the extent of their respective interests (except with respect to builders all-risk insurance and property all risk-insurance, which policies shall name the other party as ???loss payee???); (ii) provide a waiver of any rights of subrogation against the other Party; and (iii) indicate that all policies have been endorsed as described above. All policies of a Party shall be written with insurers having an A.M. Best rating no less than "A- VII". All policies shall be written on an occurrence basis. All policies of a Party shall contain an endorsement that such insurance policies shall be primary for claims arising out of such Party???s

activities regardless of like coverages, if any, carried by any other Party or its employees, agents, representatives, members, directors and officers. No Party's liability under this Agreement is limited to the amount of insurance coverage required herein by virtue of this Section. 6.11 Contractor's Insurance Requirements. For the duration of this Agreement, any contractor or subcontractor performing work on the Shared Premises shall, at its sole cost and expense, procure and maintain liability insurance policies and coverages in an amount required under the applicable service agreements or, if not specified therein, as reasonably required by the Parties and consistent with prudent industry practices. 6.12 Allocation of Insurance Proceeds. (a) Any proceeds of insurance received by a Party under the insurance policies required to be carried hereunder relating to a casualty event or event of loss with respect to a Party's Project, may be applied by such Party in its sole discretion, provided that in the event a Party receives proceeds of insurance under such insurance policies relating to a casualty event or event of loss with respect to the Common Facilities, such insurance proceeds shall be held in trust by such Party until such loss proceeds are applied to the payment of the costs of repair or restoration of the Common Facilities relating to such casualty event or event of loss, in accordance with Section 6.12(b). (b) In the event that any portion of the Common Facilities are damaged or destroyed by a casualty event, and provided the proceeds from insurance covering the damage or destruction are sufficient and available to cover the full cost of restoring the Common Facilities (excluding the amount of any deductible and/or self-insured retention as specified in the applicable insurance policy), the Parties shall arrange to rebuild the Common Facilities using such proceeds unless both Parties agree to the contrary. If there is an uninsured loss or insurance proceeds are inadequate for rebuilding, if such uninsured loss is not subject to an action for which a Party is obligated to indemnify the other Party pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, the Parties shall contribute additional amounts based on their Project Percentage Interest of the Common Facilities damaged for all costs and expenses of repair or replacement of such damaged Common Facilities unless both Parties agree to the contrary. (c) Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Parties acknowledge and agree that in the event of conflict between the terms of (1) that certain Credit and Guaranty Agreement dated as of May 11, 2012 and entered into by Alpaugh North, Alpaugh 50, GCL Alpaugh Project Holdco, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, the Lenders (under and as defined in the Credit Agreement) and Morgan Stanley Senior Funding, Inc., as Collateral Agent and as Administrative Agent for the Lenders (as amended, modified or supplemented from time to time, the ???Credit Agreement???) and (2) subsections 6.12(a-b), the terms of the Credit Agreement shall govern. ARTICLE SEVEN OPERATION AND MANAGEMENT 7.1 Operator Performance Standard. Each Party is required to operate and maintain such Party???s Project Controlled Assets acting as a prudent operator and manager and otherwise
12 DSMDB-3127047v2
(i) in accordance with good operating practice, (ii) in compliance with all Laws, and (iii) without causing a material adverse effect on the other Party or such other Party???s Project. 7.2 O&M Agreement. Pursuant to the O&M Agreement, Alpaugh North has engaged the Operator to provide for the operation, maintenance and repair of the Alpaugh North Project and the Common Facilities and the Shared Premises. (a) Alpaugh 50 hereby agrees to pay to Alpaugh North a portion of the costs paid by Alpaugh North to the Operator pursuant to the O&M Agreement for operation, maintenance and repair of the Common Facilities and the Shared Premises, which portion shall be equal to Alpaugh 50???s Project Percentage Interest of such costs (???Reimbursable O&M Costs???). For clarity, Reimburseable O&M Costs shall not include any costs payable under the O&M Agreement relating to facilities other than the Common Facilities or premises other than the Shared Premises. Alpaugh North shall use commercially reasonable efforts to cause the Operator to submit separate invoices for costs relating to operation, maintenance and repair of the Common Facilities and Shared Premises. If separate invoices are not obtainable despite such efforts, the portion of the costs payable under the O&M Agreement relating to operation, maintenance and repair of the Common Facilities and Shared Premises shall be determined by Alpaugh North in a commercially reasonable manner. (b) Payment for all expenses relating to the Shared Premises or Common Facilities that are not Reimbursable O&M Costs will be made by the responsible Party before any penalty for non-payment will be assessed and in a timely enough manner so that the Shared Premises or Common Facilities will not be jeopardized or made subject to any lien or encumbrance. Insurance Requirements
Casualty Insurance
(a) Builder???s All-Risk Insurance During Construction. During any construction each Party performing construction, shall procure or cause to be procured, and maintain or cause to be maintained, at its sole cost and expense, builder???s all-risk insurance in an amount (i) sufficient to replace any new or existing Shared Facilities which are subject to such construction, and (ii) that is reasonably acceptable to the Party performing construction. (b) Property Damage Insurance During Operations. During operations each Party shall procure or cause to be procured, and maintain or cause to be maintained, at its sole cost and expense, property damage in an amount (i) sufficient to replace any existing Shared Facilities that may be affected by a loss, and (ii) that is reasonably acceptable to the Parties. Other Insurance
(a) General Liability Insurance. At all times each Party, shall procure or cause to be procured, and maintain or cause to be maintained liability insurance covering the respective activities of the Parties on the site of the Projects or the Shared Premises, including general liability coverage and comprehensive automotive liability coverage. Such coverage shall (i) have a minimum combined occurrence and annual limitation of Ten Million Dollars ($10,000,000), and (ii) contain a blanket broad form contractual endorsement and severability of interest clause. Furthermore, if a policy is on a ???claims made??? basis, such coverage shall survive the termination of this Agreement until the expiration of the maximum statutory period of limitations in the State of California for actions based on contract or in tort. If coverage is on an ???occurrence??? basis, insurance on an occurrence basis shall be maintained for the term of this Agreement. (b) Workers Compensation. At all times, each Party shall independently obtain and maintain appropriate workers compensation insurance to provide minimum coverage to comply with any statutory obligation imposed by workers compensation or occupational disease laws.
